    "IntroductionOnline learning has traditionally been seen as an option that could benefit a particular demographic of students who are noticeably older and have more familial, financial, and employment-related commitments.",
    "The COVID-19 pandemic [1][2][3], which caught everyone off guard in December 2019, however, drastically altered the educational landscape in a matter of weeks [4].",
